    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 23, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received a letter from a Mr. J.
                    Hardcastle, stating that he has been incarcerated in the old capitol prison
                    since the 17th instant. He represents that the military authorities have been
                    very courteous and kind to him hitherto, but that he is not aware that any
                    charges have been preferred against him.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to request that you will be good enough to acquaint me with the
                    cause of his arrest and imprisonment.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most obedient,
                    humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LYONS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">W. H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                            State, &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
